LOCUS       UEA_012_(white-eye_gRNA 8466 bp ds-DNA     circular     18-JUN-2025
DEFINITION  .
COMMENT     Here is the locked registry copy of the white-eye gRNA HDR plasmid
            (UEA_012), made for Matthew's PhD.  In-silico design can be found
            here: In-Silico white-eye gRNA HDR Plasmid  This plasmid exists in
            real life, and was sequenced by ONT sequencing, files located under
            the files Matt S-C->white-ete HDR Knockin (UEA_012)->Oxford
            Nanopore Sequencing Results->Sequencing Results of UEA_012
            white-eye HDR Plasmid-> Working copy of UEA_012  This has the ONT
            sequence in context of other sequencing results.  Plasmid was
            constructed from Fluorophore of UEA_011(Angela_TRA_Guide), and the
            Backbone and gRNA of the Vasa global drive PVasa3-white_+_tra_drive
            Gibson assembly for gRNA+Backbone, and then Digestion/Ligation for
            this fragment to the fluorophore using Not1-HF and Fse1.
